  <h4 class="sp-main-title">PRIVACY INFORMATION</h4>
  <p>This is FanClash’s online privacy policy. This policy applies only to activities FanClash engages in on its website and does not apply to FanClash activities that are “offline” or unrelated to the website. FanClash collects certain anonymous data regarding the usage of the website. This information does not personally identify users, by itself or in combination with other information, and is gathered to improve the performance of the website. The anonymous data collected by the FanClash website can include information such as the type of browser you are using, your IP address and the length of the visit to the website.</p>

  <p>You may also be asked to provide personally identifiable information on the FanClash website, which may include your name, address, telephone number, credit card number, and e-mail address. This information can be gathered when feedback or e-mails are sent to FanClash, when you register for services or request additional information or literature. In all such cases you have the option of providing us with personally identifiable information, but certain functions on the website may not be available to you.</p><br />

  <h4 class="sp-main-title">COOKIES.</h4>
  <p>Cookies are small bits of data that are deposited on a user’s hard drive. The FanClash website utilizes Cookies and IP addresses for certain functions. Cookies permit users to store their password and other user information without having to constantly re-enter this data. Cookies also permits FanClash and our advertisers to tailor our website and advertising to your needs. Most browsers permit users to decline to accept Cookies, although the default setting is typically to accept them. You may choose to decline the Cookies, but certain functions of the website may not be accessible to you.</p><br />

